-- European Stocks Climb as Adecco, Luxxotica Rebound; U.S. Futures Advance
-- B y   D a v i d   M e r r i t t
-- 2010-09-23T07:05:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/european-stocks-climb-as-adecco-luxxotica-rebound-u-s-futures-advance.html
 European stocks advanced, with the
Stoxx Europe 600 Index rebounding from its biggest drop in
almost a month, as shares of Adecco SA and Luxottica Group SpA
rallied. U.S. futures gained, while Asian stocks were little
changed.  The benchmark Stoxx 600 advanced 0.6 percent, as all 19
industry groups gained. Adecco rallied 3 percent in Zurich,
while Luxottica, the world’s largest eyewear maker, gained 2.3
percent in Milan.  Futures on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index advanced 0.4
percent, while the MSCI Asia Pacific Index rose less than 0.1
percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
